Django Tutorial Extension Assignment
Overview

This project is an extension of the Django tutorial. The goal was to improve the website by adding security, configuring a domain, deploying the project, expanding the functionality, and creating a comment model.

Homework – Adding Security to Your Website

Several security improvements were added to the Django project through the settings file.

Security Settings
DEBUG = False

ALLOWED_HOSTS = ['127.0.0.1', 'localhost', 'your-app-name.herokuapp.com']

CSRF_COOKIE_SECURE = True
SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE = True
SECURE_BROWSER_XSS_FILTER = True
SECURE_CONTENT_TYPE_NOSNIFF = True
SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT = True
Password Hashing
PASSWORD_HASHERS = [
    'django.contrib.auth.hashers.PBKDF2PasswordHasher',
]

These settings help prevent:

Cross-site scripting (XSS)

Session hijacking

Unsafe cookies

Content sniffing vulnerabilities

Domain Configuration

The project domain was configured by modifying the ALLOWED_HOSTS setting in Django.

Example configuration:

ALLOWED_HOSTS = [
    'localhost',
    '127.0.0.1',
    'your-app-name.herokuapp.com'
]

If a custom domain is used, it can be added like this:

ALLOWED_HOSTS = [
    'www.mysite.com',
    'mysite.com'
]
